	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Wed 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Tammuz&#44; 1844</date></p>
				<p rend="align(right)">&#40;<date>August</date>&#41;</p>
				<p>Dear Friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Herewith you will receive the brief&#44;<lb/> article against &#8220;the men of the West&#8221;.<lb/> Please study it carefully. It should make<lb/> a resounding impression. Only through<lb/> such small doses of <hi rend="underline">assa</hi> <hi rend="underline">faedita</hi><lb/> <add>unadorned vulgarity</add> can one have<lb/> an effect. The indolent American<lb/> public does not read logical<lb/> presentations. The conclusion is<lb/> certainly true. At most&#44; an observation<lb/> and its accompanying empty phrase<lb/> is heard by these people and makes<lb/> an impression upon them.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am looking forward to your reply</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">your sincerely</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName></p>
				<p>P.S. At the same time you will find a<lb/> brief correspondence for the Occident</p>
		</body>
